<title>HONG KONG: Hong Kong Bank of Canada Q1 net up 28 pct.</title>
<headline>Hong Kong Bank of Canada Q1 net up 28 pct.</headline>
<dateline>HONG KONG 1997-02-24</dateline>
<text>
<p>Hong Kong Bank of Canada, an indirectly wholly-owned unit of HSBC Holdings Plc, posted net profit of C$31.0 million for the first quarter ended January 31, against C$24.2 million in the same 1995/96 period.</p>
<p>Three-months ended January 31 (in millions of Canadian</p>
<p>dollars unless otherwise stated):</p>
<p>    Net income per common share (CAD dollar)   0.11  vs     0.09</p>
<p>    Net interest income			     122.4  vs    113.7</p>
<p>    Other income					 50.8  vs     34.8</p>
<p>    Net interest and other income		 162.9  vs    133.5</p>
<p>	 (including provision for credit losses)</p>
<p>    Net income					   31.0  vs     24.2</p>
<p>    Total assets				   21,792.0  vs 19,374.0</p>
<p>    Total capital ratio (percent)		   9.4  vs	9.5</p>
<p>    Tier 1 capital ratio (percent)		  5.1  vs	5.4</p>
<p>-- Hong Kong Newsroom (852) 2843 6441</p>
